{
  "description": "A top-down view of clear, turquoise water flowing over a rocky seabed. The rocks are varied in size, shape, and color, ranging from dark brown and grey to lighter beige and tan. The water is remarkably transparent, allowing for a clear view of the rocks beneath. Sunlight creates shimmering patterns on the rocks and the surface of the water, highlighting the texture of both. The image captures the contrast between the solid, earthy rocks and the fluid, cool water. The transition between the rocks and the water is seamless, creating a sense of depth and tranquility.",
